pos_mean_info_list.mean: 气态的，气体的；无实质的

bilingual.source: A balloon will go higher or lower depending on how much gas is burned.
bilingual.target: 气球的升降取决于燃烧了多少气体。

bilingual.source: Using marsh gas can reduce greenhouse gas emissions.
bilingual.target: 使用沼气可以减少温室气体排放。
你能闻到这种气体的味道吗？
煤气炉使用气体作为燃料。

bilingual.source: By using gas chromatography, we can analyze gas samples.
bilingual.target: 通过气相色谱法，我们可以分析气体样品。
溴化氢是一种无色气体。

bilingual.source: Chl gas can be dangerous if inhaled.
bilingual.target: 吸入氯气体可能是危险的。

bilingual.source: Neptune is made up of gas and ice.
bilingual.target: 海王星是由气体和冰组成的。
乙烷是一种无色无味的气体。

list.abstract: GAS（generaladaptationsyndrome）全身适应综合征。劣性应激原持续作用于机体，应激可表现为一个动态的连续过程，并可最终导致内环境紊乱和疾病。可分为：警觉期、抵抗期、衰竭期。
中国CS届的网络红人，人称虎神。因枪法凶悍，经常被称作弊，算是CS1.6没落的年代，国内最火的草根玩家，与4357等人齐名。 出身日期：1996 游戏名称：CS1.6（反恐精英1.6）

yingyinNormal.en: The plant leaves are now releasing the gas.
yingyinNormal.zh: 植株的叶片开始释放出警告气体。

yingyinNormal.en: A lot of other gas smells… Oh, the humanity.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，很多气体都有味道…还有没有人性啊。

yingyinNormal.en: What is the sixth noble gas? What? You said you're a scientist. What is the sixth noble gas?
yingyinNormal.zh: 第六惰性气体是什么？什么？你说你是科学家，第六惰性气体是什么？

yingyinNormal.en: We're here to make milk. That's what we're good at. But as a byproduct, you know, when those cows are pooping, we're making this gas that's not a good greenhouse gas.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们来这儿挤奶，这是我们擅长的事，但作为副产品，你要知道这些奶牛什么时候大便，我们现在制的气体不是很好的温室气体。

yingyinNormal.en: The gas triggers a change in the biological activity in the two neighboring plants.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这种气体激发了旁边两株植物的一系列的生化反应。

yingyinNormal.en: They're finding that when plants are attacked, they also release an unseen gas from their leaves.
yingyinNormal.zh: 它们发现当植物被攻击时，它们会从叶子中释放一种无色无味的气体。

yingyinNormal.en: A black hole's accretion disk is made up of gas and dust and magnetic fields that spin at high speeds radiating heat and light.
yingyinNormal.zh: 黑洞的吸积盘是由气体、尘埃和磁场组成，并以高速旋转发射出光和热。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I think you can count on a lot of flaming gas, which is what you would have gotten from your first choice, Neil deGrasse Tyson.
yingyinNormal.zh: 肯定会有很多可燃气体接踵而来，如果你的首选之人尼尔·德格拉斯·泰森有来，也会有很多[放屁]。

yingyinNormal.en: These models are made of cardboard. But the real planets are made of rock and ice and gas. But of course the moon is made of cheese.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些模型是用纸板做的。但是真正的行星是由岩石，冰块和气体构成的。但是我认为月球是由奶酪组成的。

yingyinNormal.en: Eventually, the universe will run out of gas to form stars, and the stars themselves will run out of fuel and burn out, leaving the universe with only black holes in it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 最终，宇宙将会由于缺少气体而无法形成恒星，同时恒星自身也会燃烧殆尽，宇宙中留下的只会是一个个黑洞。

yingyinNormal.en: So, what is the universe made of? The universe contains all the things that we can see, like stars, gas, and planets. We call these things ordinary or baryonic matter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那么，宇宙是由什么构成的呢？宇宙中包含着我们肉眼所能看到的一切，比如恒星、气体和行星。我们称这些为普通物质或重子物质。

yingyinNormal.en: If we don't patch it up, the propulsion tank will overflow and flood the ship with poisonous gas! This? Yes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果我们不把漏气的地方补上，毒气会从气箱里漫出来，有毒气体会充满整艘飞船！这个？是的。

yingyinNormal.en: No, actually, I think that they're, gas. Gas? Wow. Intense.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不是，其实是瓦斯炉。瓦斯炉？真带劲。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, barnacles. I'm out of gas?
yingyinNormal.zh: 该死，没汽油了？
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《The SpongeBob Movie: Sponge Out of Water》

yingyinNormal.en: I don't think there's much gas, old sport.
yingyinNormal.zh: 汽油恐怕不多了，老伙计。

yingyinNormal.en: At that temperature, natural gas is transformed into liquefied natural gas, or LNG, 600 times smaller in volume.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在此温度下,天然气转变为液体天然气或液化天然气，这样体积就缩小了600倍。

yingyinNormal.en: You guys are the last to get natural gas as it's coming through the pipes. Everyone else is taking the gas before it gets to you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们是最晚得到天然气的，因为要从管道输送过来，在你们有天然气之前大家都有了。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, you know that smell gas has? Yeah. They put that in.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道瓦斯的味道吗？知道那是加进去的。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, man, he almost hit a gas truck. Do you ever watch Baywatch?
yingyinNormal.zh: 天啊，他差点撞上油罐车。你看不看“海滩游侠”？

yingyinNormal.en: And everybody else is taking gas along the way. All the big cities in the northeast, all those places are taking the gas before it gets to Boston.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其他人也一直使用天然气，所有东北部的大城市在天然气到达波士顿之前，这些地方都有了天然气。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: But they're also from birds that live on farms using regenerative agriculture-special techniques to cultivate rich soils that can trap greenhouse <highlight>gases</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但它们也来自使用特殊再生农业技术的农场，这些农场能培育出捕获温室气体的肥沃土壤。

examination_example.sentence: Fossil fuels — coal, oil, <highlight>gas</highlight> — still generate roughly 85 percent of the world's energy supply.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 化石燃料——煤、石油、天然气——仍约占全球能源供应的85%。

examination_example.sentence: How the warming of the Earth from greenhouse <highlight>gases</highlight> is leading to conditions that worsen fires.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 温室气体导致的地球变暖是如何导致火灾恶化的。

word_usage.usage:
gas作名词指“气体”时，即可用作可数名词，也可用作不可数名词，复数指多种气体。例：
Air is a mixture of gases.
空气为混合气体。

gas作名词指“燃气；煤气”时，是不可数名词。例：
Coal is actually cheaper than gas.
煤实际上比煤气便宜。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The erupting <highlight>gas</highlight> might endanger local children.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 喷发的气体可能会危及当地儿童。

examination_example.sentence: The massive <highlight>gas</highlight> underground.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 地下大量的气体。

examination_example.sentence: There was a hill where <highlight>gas</highlight> leakage was so noticeable that schoolboys would sometimes set the hill on fire.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有一座山，气体泄漏非常明显，以至于学生们有时会放火烧山。

examination_example.sentence: Unless current greenhouse <highlight>gas</highlight> emissions drop, 70 percent of king penguins will be forced to relocate their breeding grounds, or face extinction.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 除非当前的温室气体排放量下降，否则将有70％的帝企鹅被迫迁移繁殖地，或者将面临灭绝。

examination_example.sentence: Fewer than 4% of countries are responsible for more than half of the world's greenhouse <highlight>gas</highlight> emissions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 地球上不到4%的国家却排放了全球一半以上的温室气体。

word_usage.usage: gas 作 "汽油" 是美式英语, 等于英式英语中的 gasoline。

examination_example.sentence: The road was covered with spilled <highlight>gas</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 道路被溢出的汽油覆盖。

examination_example.sentence: A study by the University of Manchester calculated the emissions of CO2-the main greenhouse <highlight>gas</highlight> responsible for climate change-at every stage of microwaves, from manufacture to waste disposal.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 曼彻斯特大学的一项研究计算了微波炉从生产到废物处理整个过程中在每个阶段的二氧化碳排放量——二氧化碳是引起气候变化的主要温室气体。

examination_example.sentence: It is profitable to drill to depths more than 1,000 feet for oil and <highlight>gas</highlight> extraction, but only recently in California has it become profitable to pump water from this depth.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 钻探超过1,000英尺的深度进行石油和天然气开采是有利可图的，但是直到最近，在加利福尼亚州才从这种深度抽水变得有利可图。

examination_example.sentence: Neon makes orange, while other <highlight>gases</highlight> make yellow or blue.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 氖产生橙色，而其他气体产生黄色或蓝色。

examination_example.sentence: They fill these tubes with <highlight>gases</highlight> that glow when electrified.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们将通电后会发光的气体注入这些玻璃管中。

word_usage.usage: gas 作 "汽油" 是美式英语, 等于英式英语中的 gasoline。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: How long until they go the way of <highlight>gas</highlight> street lamps and morning milk deliveries?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们还要多久才能走上有煤气路灯、早晨可以送牛奶的路？

examination_example.sentence: It is as important as the <highlight>gas</highlight> light.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它和煤气灯一样重要。

examination_example.sentence: Thankfully, Jeff stayed calm and turned off the <highlight>gas</highlight> quickly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 谢天谢地，杰夫保持冷静，迅速关掉了煤气。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Gas</highlight> will be covered for each delivery.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每次送货都要付汽油的费用。

examination_example.sentence: It flies using a 23-gallon tank of <highlight>gas</highlight> and bums 5 gallons per hour in the air.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其油箱容积为23加仑，飞行耗油为每小时5加仑。

word_usage.usage: gas 作 "汽油" 是美式英语，等于英式英语中的 gasoline。

examination_example.sentence: Basically, an electric car can go twice as far as a <highlight>gas</highlight> car for the same price.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 基本上，同样的价格，一辆电动车的续航能力是一辆汽油车的两倍。

examination_example.sentence: There are plenty of <highlight>gas</highlight> stations, but not many charging stations for electric cars.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 加油站很多，但电动车充电站不多。

examination_example.sentence: She often forgot to turn off the <highlight>gas</highlight> and the food she was cooking usually got burnt.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她经常忘记关煤气，她做的食物经常被烧焦。
